Package com.credenceid.biometrics

Interface Biometrics

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BiometricsActivity, BiometricsManager
    public interface Biometrics
    Interface provides access to Credence ID SDK Biometric APIs.

    May be accessed by extending an activity from BiometricsActivity instead of android.app.Activity.

    For more flexibility, instantiate an instance of the BiometricsManager object in your activity.

      • initializeBiometrics

        void initializeBiometrics​(Biometrics.OnInitializedListener listener)
        Initializes Biometrics SDK. Notifies CredenceService to bind to calling application.

        This API must first be called before calling any other CredenceSDK API. Failure to do so will result in FAIL error codes for every other API.

        Parameters:
        listener - Callback to be invoked on initialization result.

      • finalizeBiometrics

        void finalizeBiometrics​(boolean stop_service)
        Informs Biometrics SDK that it is no longer being used by calling application. Calling this function, regardless of param value, will by DEFAULT unbind CredenceService from current application. If service is shutdown, Service must be re-initialized before it may be used again throughout ANY application.
        Parameters:
        stop_service - If true, force the CredenceService to unbind and SHUTDOWN otherwise ONLY unbind.

      • hasFMDMatcher

        boolean hasFMDMatcher()
        Checks to see if device supports creating FMD templates and FMD matching from fingerprint Bitmap images returned by any of the following APIs:

        grabFingerprint(ScanType, OnFingerprintGrabbedFullListener)

        grabFingerprint(ScanType, boolean, OnFingerprintGrabbedFullListener) }

        grabFingerprint(ScanType, OnFingerprintGrabbedListener) }

        grabFingerprint(ScanType, boolean, OnFingerprintGrabbedListener) }

        grabFingerprint(ScanType, OnFingerprintGrabbedWSQListener) }

        grabFingerprint(ScanType, boolean, OnFingerprintGrabbedWSQListener) }

        grabFingerprint(ScanType, boolean, OnFingerprintGrabbedRawListener) }

        Returns:
        True if device supports FMD creation and matching, otherwise false.

        void cardCloseCommand()
        Requests Credence ID Service to turn off card reader peripheral.

        If this API is called and a Biometrics.CardReaderStatusListener callback was registered either through

        cardOpenCommand(CardReaderStatusListener) or

        registerCardStatusListener(OnCardStatusListener) then

        callback will be invoked.

        Biometrics.ResultCode value inside callback may take on following values:

        Status.OK f card reader was closed.

        Biometrics.ResultCode.FAIL if card reader could not be closed or device does not contain a card reader.

      • grabFingerprintSync

        FingerprintSyncResponse grabFingerprintSync​(int timeout)
        Synchronously starts a fingerprint capture process. This is a blocking call; will block until fingerprint capture is completed, fails, or specified timeout period elapses. Internally this API call makes an asynchronous call and then waits for a result back. In the case result takes longer then four seconds to return, Android would throw an ANR. In order to get around this, we allow a timeout period to be specified, meaning for how long should method wait for a response back, before returning back to client.

        This API only supports ScanType.SINGLE_FINGER.

        Before calling this API, fingerprint sensor must be opened using openFingerprintReader(FingerprintReaderStatusListener fingerprintReaderStatusListener) API.

        Parameters:
        timeout - Time period to wait in milliseconds for operation to complete before returning with fail.
        Returns:
        FingerprintSyncResponse
